#compdef meowlnir
# ============================================================================
# meowlnir - Matrix moderation bot for Mjolnir-style policy enforcement (Go, AGPL-3.0)
#
# Author : Tulir Asokan (maunium)
# Upstream: https://github.com/maunium/meowlnir
#
# meowlnir is a Matrix moderation bot that consumes Mjolnir / Draupnir
# policy-list rooms and applies bans, redactions, server ACL updates,
# and message-redaction policies across many protected rooms in
# parallel. Designed for the workload of moderating large public
# Matrix spaces (matrix.org room directory, federated communities)
# where centralized moderation policy + decentralized enforcement
# across many rooms is the operational model.
#
# CLI flags:
#   -c, --config <path>                 - config YAML (default config.yaml)
#   -n, --no-update                     - don't write back config-format upgrades
#   -e, --generate-example-config       - emit example config and quit
#   -v, --version                       - print version
#   -h, --help                          - print help
#
# The Matrix lane is built on `maunium.net/go/mautrix v0.28.0`
# (declared verbatim at upstream go.mod HEAD), the canonical Go
# Matrix Client-Server SDK by Tulir Asokan (mautrix.org, github.com/
# mautrix/go, 620+ stars). The mautrix/go SDK implements the full
# Matrix Client-Server API + Application Service API + appservice
# encryption (Olm + Megolm via libolm bindings) + state-sync v3 +
# sliding-sync + the entire room-event taxonomy (200+ event types
# including custom moderation events). It is the canonical Go
# Matrix SDK and the dependency-of-record for the entire mautrix
# bridges family (mautrix-whatsapp, mautrix-telegram, mautrix-
# signal, mautrix-discord, mautrix-bluesky, etc.) plus moderation
# bots like meowlnir.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 217 :: MATRIX CLIENT-SERVER API (matrix.org spec, end-to-end encrypted chat)
# Round 1350 :: Go slot 2 of 4 :: continues Axis 217
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : matrix-org/matrix-rust-sdk            [R1349 _errornowatcher]
#   Go      : mautrix/go                            [R1350 THIS FILE]
#   TS/Node : matrix-org/matrix-js-sdk              [R1351 closing]
#
# The Go lane's canonical mautrix/go is the only one of the three
# that is not directly maintained by matrix-org - it's maintained
# by the mautrix bridges org (Tulir Asokan) but treated by
# matrix-org as the canonical Go implementation. matrix-rust-sdk
# is the cross-platform encryption + sync engine used by Element X
# (mobile + new web), and matrix-js-sdk is the older engine inside
# the original Element Web client.
#
# Round-number landmark R1350.
# ============================================================================

_meowlnir() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '(-c --config)'{-c,--config}'[config YAML file (default config.yaml)]:file:_files -g "*.yaml"' \
        '(-n --no-update)'{-n,--no-update}'[do not write back config format upgrades]' \
        '(-e --generate-example-config)'{-e,--generate-example-config}'[emit example config and exit]' \
        '(- *)'{-v,--version}'[print version]' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]'
}

_meowlnir "$@"
